In Tailwind CSS, you don’t usually override classes directly like traditional CSS.

Instead, you customize Tailwind using `tailwind.config.js`. ey file ke root folder e rakhte hobe , src folder na

You can:

- Change default colors
- Modify spacing scale
- Change breakpoints
- Adjust font sizes

Then add @config "../../tailwind.config.js"; this in inout.css file


----------------------------
JIT = Just-In-Time engine in Tailwind CSS.
It uses tree shaking to reduce the bundle size.
----------------------------
## `tailwind.config.js`

- config শুধু value define করে
- component বানায় না 

Theme define (global design system)

color: primary, secondary
spacing, font, breakpoint

 project জুড়ে consistent use

use: same value everywhere দরকার

---

##  `@layer base`

default style (auto apply)

 h1, p, body style

use: basic reset / default look

---

##  `@layer components`

reusable UI class

 `.btn`, `.card`

use: same design বারবার লাগবে

---

## `@layer utilities`

custom small helper class

`.text-shadow`, `.flex-center`

use: Tailwind এ না থাকলে add করা

---

##  `:root` (CSS variable)

dynamic value control

theme switch (dark/light)

use: runtime change দরকার হলে



